---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Research | The Canary Institute" description="Research publications and focus areas at The Canary Institute.">
  <h1>Research</h1>

  <section class="section">
    <h2>Focus Areas</h2>
    <p>
      Our research spans several interconnected domains critical to
      understanding and managing the risks posed by advanced AI systems. We
      prioritize work that is both technically rigorous and actionable for
      policymakers and the public.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <h3>AI Capabilities &amp; Trajectory</h3>
    <p>
      Tracking and analyzing the pace of progress in frontier AI systems,
      including evaluations of autonomous capabilities, reasoning benchmarks,
      and the rate at which AI systems are approaching or exceeding human
      performance across critical domains. Understanding where we are on the
      capability curve is essential to calibrating the urgency of safety and
      governance interventions.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <h3>Economic Impact Analysis</h3>
    <p>
      Modeling the near- and medium-term economic consequences of AI
      deployment, including labor market disruption, productivity effects,
      wealth concentration, and the macroeconomic implications of rapid
      automation. These analyses aim to inform policy responses that ensure the
      benefits of AI are broadly shared.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <h3>Alignment &amp; Control</h3>
    <p>
      Surveying and synthesizing the state of research on ensuring AI systems
      pursue intended objectives and remain under meaningful human oversight as
      they scale. This includes interpretability, robustness under
      distributional shift, and the fundamental challenge of maintaining control
      over systems that may exceed human cognitive capabilities.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <h3>Governance &amp; Standards</h3>
    <p>
      Evaluating existing and proposed regulatory frameworks for AI, developing
      concrete policy recommendations, and designing evaluation standards that
      can keep pace with rapid capability gains. We draw on precedents from
      nuclear governance, biosecurity, and other domains where powerful
      technologies required coordinated international oversight.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <h2>Publications</h2>
    <p>
      Our first working papers and technical analyses are currently in
      preparation, including evaluations of frontier model capabilities and
      projected economic impacts. Publications will be listed here as they
      become available, with accompanying public-facing summaries on our
      <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}blog/`}>blog</a>.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
